## Phase 2 — Notion Tracking Board

### Board Setup

If the designer doesn't have a Notion board yet, create one using the Notion MCP tools.
The board is a **database** with these properties:

| Property | Type | Options / Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Role Title** | Title | e.g. "Senior Product Designer" |
| **Company** | Text | Company name |
| **Status** | Select | Bookmarked → Applying → Applied → Screening → Interview → Offer → Rejected → Withdrawn |
| **Applied Date** | Date | Date application was submitted |
| **Deadline** | Date | Application deadline if known |
| **Job URL** | URL | Link to the original posting |
| **Source** | Select | LinkedIn / Dribbble / Referral / Telegram / Direct / Other |
| **Location** | Text | City, Remote, Hybrid |
| **Salary Range** | Text | e.g. "€70–85k" or "£55–65k" |
| **Job Description** | Text (long) | Full copy of the JD (paste here) |
| **CV Version** | Text | Which CV variant was used (e.g. "CV_SaaS_v3") |
| **Cover Letter** | Checkbox | Was a cover letter written? |
| **Portfolio Sent** | Checkbox | Was portfolio included? |
| **Company Research** | Text (long) | Research notes (product, culture, team, funding) |
| **Contacts** | Text | Recruiter name, LinkedIn URL, email |
| **Notes** | Text (long) | Interview notes, rejections reasons, follow-ups |
| **Priority** | Select | 🔥 High / ⭐ Medium / 🧊 Low |
| **Next Action** | Text | e.g. "Follow up by Fri" / "Prepare case study" |

### Recommended Views

Set up these views in the Notion database:

- **Kanban by Status** — primary view, drag cards as status changes
- **Table — All Applications** — sortable, good for bulk review
- **Filter: Active** — Status is not Rejected/Withdrawn
- **Filter: This Week** — Applied Date is this week
- **Gallery — Companies** — visual overview with company logos

### Adding a New Job Entry

When asked to add a job to Notion:

1. Create a new page in the database
2. Fill: Role Title, Company, Status (start at "Bookmarked" or "Applying"), Job URL, Source, Location
3. Paste the full job description into the **Job Description** field
4. Set Priority based on the designer's enthusiasm + fit score
5. Set **Next Action** to the immediate next step

